Should you need further assistance, or if you would like to share more of your journey with us, please message us at gethelp@betterme.world. Have a pleasant day! Kind Regards, Team BetterMe', 'modified': '2023-03-21T16:30:37Z'}

{'id': 27827539, 'body': "Hello!
Thank you for your feedback, and we appreciate your honest opinion!
Posting a review is not the obligatory yet pretty important thing for us. The BetterMe Team always listens to our customer's minds, and we are doing everything possible to improve our services based on your feedback.
We are genuinely happy to hear your thoughts about the app, its tools, and our services overall.

The Meals Plans are designed by professional nutritionists and created to be as healthy as they are diverse. They are suggested to you according to your quiz answer and calibrated according to your preferences, current details, and goals.
Still, if you do not like the meals suggested in the plan, you can always do the following:
1) Open the BetterMe app;
2) Tap More at the bottom of your screen;
3) Tap Meals;
4) Substitute the recipe suggested in your meal plan by selecting and logging a meal from any other day.

Another alternative is to log food that is not on your meal plan. To do this, please go to the Plan tab at the bottom and select the Add Food option. Then choose a mealtime, tap Add Food and proceed with logging your meals.

Yet another option is to substitute some of the ingredients. You can let us know if you need our help finding the correct substitution.
You can even change the suggested Diet Type:
- open the BetterMe app;
- tap More at the bottom;
- select Meals from the list;
- tap More Info 'i' in the upper right-hand corner;
- select the Change Meal Plan button and choose your diet type;
- hit Next;
- confirm your choice by selecting the meal plan and tapping the Get Meal Plan button.

We are also happy to see that you liked the workouts. It's quite an essential part of the overall plan, and you can always find something suitable for your needs.
You can follow the suggested workouts from the Plan section or select any additional or alternative exercises from the Workout section.
You can also schedule or edit the workout reminders:
- open the BetterMe app;
- select More ‚Üí Profile;
- scroll down and find the Workout reminders button.

As for the Calorie Tracker, we are continuously expanding our barcode database. It may currently not be as extensive as we would desire, and we are on the way to making it better. We understand it is a time-consuming process, and we appreciate your patience. 
In the meantime, I can suggest using a workaround with manual food logging:
- go to the Plan tab and tap the Add Food option;
- choose a mealtime; 
- hit Add Food and proceed with logging your meals. 

We hope that our services will bring a lot of enjoyment and positive impressions to you!
You can also contact us at gethelp@betterme.tips if you have any questions about the app.
Stay safe and healthy!
Kind regards, Team BetterMe", 'modified': '2022-02-03T12:29:21Z'}

